            <title><![CDATA[From Engine to Hylozoa Engine]]></title>
            <link>https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa</link>
            <guid>https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa</guid>
            <pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[The project has been ongoing since since March 2025, let's review its current state together:]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The project has been ongoing since since March 2025, let's review its current state together:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" alt="Beach demo scene" src="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/assets/images/DemoBeach-a50bfa432c9e368d6502a19acbe620a3.gif" width="1919" height="1113" class="img_ev3q"></p>
<h6 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="runs-smoother-outside-of-a-gif"><em>runs smoother outside of a gif</em><a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#runs-smoother-outside-of-a-gif" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to runs-smoother-outside-of-a-gif" title="Direct link to runs-smoother-outside-of-a-gif" translate="no">​</a></h6>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="overview">Overview<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#overview" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Overview" title="Direct link to Overview" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Hylozoa-Engine runs on a ECS and currently supports the following components</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="featurescomponents">Features/Components<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#featurescomponents" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Features/Components" title="Direct link to Features/Components" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="prefabs">Prefabs<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#prefabs" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Prefabs" title="Direct link to Prefabs" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Users can save an entity config as a .json to instanciate it whenever they need.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="lua-scripting">Lua scripting<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#lua-scripting" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Lua scripting" title="Direct link to Lua scripting" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Users can write lua scripts to control their entity.<br>
<!-- -->The following methods are currently exposed:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><code>instanciate()</code> to instanciate an entity from a prefab</li>
<li class=""><code>destroy()</code> to destroy an entity</li>
<li class=""><code>get_transform()</code> to get the transform of an entity</li>
<li class=""><code>is_key_pressed()</code> to check if the user pressed a key</li>
</ul>
<p>The standard <code>math</code> library is also exposed.<br>
<!-- -->And the following entrypoint is read from the script by the game engine:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><code>onUpdate(entity, deltatime)</code> logic to run every frame</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="planned-improvements">Planned improvements<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#planned-improvements" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Planned improvements" title="Direct link to Planned improvements" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">A way to communication between entities' scripts to coordinate them</li>
<li class="">Lua entrypoint for the following events:<!-- -->
<ul>
<li class="">Collision detection</li>
<li class="">Entity emotion change</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="renderable">Renderable<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#renderable" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Renderable" title="Direct link to Renderable" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Entity can have a sprite or a colored shape attached to them.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="planned-improvements-1">Planned improvements<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#planned-improvements-1" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Planned improvements" title="Direct link to Planned improvements" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>The entity's sprite will be animated.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="physics-simulation">Physics simulation<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#physics-simulation" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Physics simulation" title="Direct link to Physics simulation" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Entities with a RigidBody will be affected by gravity and collides with other collider components.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="noise-listener">Noise listener<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#noise-listener" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Noise listener" title="Direct link to Noise listener" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Entity <em>(even the camera)</em> will hear the noises comming from the scene depending on the distance from the source.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="from-engine-to-hylozoa-engine">From Engine to Hylozoa Engine<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#from-engine-to-hylozoa-engine" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to From Engine to Hylozoa Engine" title="Direct link to From Engine to Hylozoa Engine" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Hylozoa Engine has a solid foundation, but it lacks any features that helps to build complex ecosystems.</p>
<p>Therefore, the following updates are planned for the comming year:</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="prefab-parenting">Prefab parenting<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#prefab-parenting" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Prefab parenting" title="Direct link to Prefab parenting" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>Following evolution, species have inherited traits from their parent species.<br>
<!-- -->As such, using prefabs parenting would allow the users to mimic this aspect of evolution.</p>
<p>Example:<br>
<code>Ape</code>
|
<code>Monkey</code>
|-&gt;    <code>Jungle Monkey</code><br>
<!-- -->|-&gt;    <code>Beach Monkey</code></p>
<p>AND <code>Crab</code> -&gt; <code>Beach Monkey</code></p>
<p><code>BeachMonkey.prefab.json</code>:</p>
<div class="language-json codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-json codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">{</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:#36acaa">"prefab"</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">{</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        </span><span class="token property" style="color:#36acaa">"parents"</span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">:</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">[</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">            </span><span class="token string" style="color:#e3116c">"Monkey"</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">            </span><span class="token string" style="color:#e3116c">"Crab"</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">]</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">}</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">,</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    </span><span class="token property" style="color:#36acaa">"components"</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">:</span><span class="token plain"> ...</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">}</span><br></div></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Such that (<code>Ape</code> &lt; <code>Monkey</code> &lt; <code>Crab</code>) + beach monkey fields == <code>Beach Monkey</code>.</p>
<p>Proposal:<br>
<!-- -->We simply add a <code>prefab.parent</code> field to the prefab's json.<br>
<!-- -->We then construct the child's prefab by parsing every parent and overwriting over the previous parent's fields.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="senses-components">Senses components<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#senses-components" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Senses components" title="Direct link to Senses components" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="view">View<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#view" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to View" title="Direct link to View" translate="no">​</a></h4>
<p>We don't support vision yet.<br>
<!-- -->This will be done using simple raycasts.<br>
<!-- -->The following methods will be provided to scripts:</p>
<div class="language-lua codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-lua codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">OnSightEnter(); -- 1st frame</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">OnSightLeave(); -- 1st frame of not seeing after being seen</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">OnSight(); -- All other frames</span><br></div></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="scripting">Scripting<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#scripting" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Scripting" title="Direct link to Scripting" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="listing-surrounding-entities">Listing surrounding entities<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#listing-surrounding-entities" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Listing surrounding entities" title="Direct link to Listing surrounding entities" translate="no">​</a></h4>
<p>Example: an entity should know how many friend or foe surrounds it to make fight-or-flight decision.</p>
<p>Proposal: <code>PerceptionMemory</code> component</p>
<p>The <code>PerceptionMemory</code> component make use of all senses that are attached to the entity as components (hear, see, smell).
Internally, it will store every entity perceived and their time of perception whenever the senses triggers.<br>
<!-- -->The method <code>get_perception-list() : {entity}</code> will be available to retrieve a list of entity perceived in the last <code>memoryTime</code> seconds.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="ground-rework">Ground rework<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#ground-rework" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Ground rework" title="Direct link to Ground rework" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>Currently, creating ground is a bit of a hassle.</p>
<p>Proposal: Constructing terrain from a .svg.<br>
<!-- -->That method has already proven itself in games such as Super Mario Wonder.<br>
<!-- -->This would be stored in the scene's configuration and not as an entity.
Colors can be configured to act as different materials (dirt, sand, water, ...).</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="default-assetsprefabs">Default assets/prefabs<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/road-to-hylozoa#default-assetsprefabs" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Default assets/prefabs" title="Direct link to Default assets/prefabs" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>To ease the user experience, default prefabs should be included.</p>
<p>Proposal:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Default hylozoa mascot entity with all perception components active.</li>
<li class="">Default random man that is player controlled.</li>
<li class="">A pixar like funny ball to show physics.</li>
<li class="">Some default ground (might be scene config or prefab).</li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>Epitech Innovative Project</category>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Mermaid for easy schemas]]></title>
            <link>https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/mermaid</link>
            <guid>https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/mermaid</guid>
            <pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Schemas configured as code]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="schemas-configured-as-code">Schemas configured as code<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/mermaid#schemas-configured-as-code" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Schemas configured as code" title="Direct link to Schemas configured as code" translate="no">​</a></h4>
<p>As the saying goes, an image is worth a thousand words...<br>
<!-- -->Whenever I tried to create schema before, I always had trouble keeping it up-to-date and had to drop it :(<br>
<!-- -->But no longer thanks to Mermaid !</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="what-is-mermaid-">What is Mermaid ?<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/mermaid#what-is-mermaid-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What is Mermaid ?" title="Direct link to What is Mermaid ?" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>Mermaid is a language to create schmas.<br>
<!-- -->No long are you stuck editing PNGs !</p>
<p>You can access the online tool <a href="https://mermaid.ai/app/projects/6c38f33b-3b7d-40c4-ab9d-e647b98da993/diagrams/990549d1-222d-4321-b2b0-89609357d2f0/version/v0.1/edit?shouldShowPopup=true" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">here</a>.
And the project's GitHub <a href="https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid/blob/develop/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">here</a>.</p>
<p>What's even better, <code>mmd</code> <em>(mermaid markdown)</em> <strong>is supported in GitHub Readme !</strong></p>
<h6 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="its-unfortunatly-not-supported-by-docusaurus-">it's unfortunatly not supported by Docusaurus :(<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/mermaid#its-unfortunatly-not-supported-by-docusaurus-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to it's unfortunatly not supported by Docusaurus :(" title="Direct link to it's unfortunatly not supported by Docusaurus :(" translate="no">​</a></h6>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="example">Example<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/mermaid#example" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Example" title="Direct link to Example" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" alt="Mermaid example" src="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/assets/images/Mermaid-example-94956245ce242ba0a2456b625b693542.svg" width="969" height="427" class="img_ev3q"></p>
<p>And here is the associated code, that you can copy paste and easily edit!</p>
<div class="language-mermaid.js codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-mermaid.js codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">---</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">config:</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  layout: elk</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  theme: mc</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  look: classic</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">---</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">classDiagram</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">direction LR</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	namespace HylozoaCompany2077 {</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        class Employee {</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +int employeeId</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +String position</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +double salary</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +work(hours: int) : void</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +requestLeave(days: int) : bool</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        }</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        class Report {</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +String title</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +Date generatedOn</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +String content</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +export(format: String) : bool</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        }</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        class Rulian {</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +String specialty</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +customMethod() : void</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        }</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        class Person:::someclass {</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        lol name</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +int age</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +String address</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +greet() : void</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	        +updateAddress(newAddress: String) : void</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        }</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	}</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    Person --&gt; Employee</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    Employee o.. "entrypoint" Report : draft</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    Person &lt;-- Rulian</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">	classDef someclass fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px;</span><br></div></code></pre></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
            <category>Tools</category>
            <category>Non-Technical</category>
