        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Measuring and Optimizing Technical Performance]]></title>
            <link>https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization</link>
            <guid>https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization</guid>
            <pubDate>Sat, 01 Mar 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Find here our plan regarding Hylozoa's testing and optimizing goals.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="find-here-our-plan-regarding-hylozoas-testing-and-optimizing-goals">Find here our plan regarding Hylozoa's testing and optimizing goals.<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#find-here-our-plan-regarding-hylozoas-testing-and-optimizing-goals" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Find here our plan regarding Hylozoa's testing and optimizing goals." title="Direct link to Find here our plan regarding Hylozoa's testing and optimizing goals." translate="no">​</a></h4>
<h1>📏 Metrics</h1>
<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="our-current-goal-is-to-track-the-following-3-metrics">Our current goal is to track the following 3 metrics:<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#our-current-goal-is-to-track-the-following-3-metrics" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Our current goal is to track the following 3 metrics:" title="Direct link to Our current goal is to track the following 3 metrics:" translate="no">​</a></h4>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="memory-usage">Memory usage<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#memory-usage" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Memory usage" title="Direct link to Memory usage" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>The following sub-metrics will be tracked</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Current Memory</li>
<li class="">Peak Memory</li>
<li class="">Memory Budget</li>
<li class="">Allocation count</li>
</ul>
<p>in 4 scenes:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Empty scene.</li>
<li class="">Beach demo scene.</li>
<li class="">A Stress scene that is overloaded with entities.</li>
<li class="">A streming scene that is constantly loading and unloading entities.</li>
</ul>
<p>For a duration of 10 seconds.</p>
<p>CI will fail is a commit introduce an unjustified spike in any of these metrics.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="cpu-usage">CPU Usage<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#cpu-usage" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to CPU Usage" title="Direct link to CPU Usage" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>We will track these sub-metrics:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Frame Time<!-- -->
<ul>
<li class="">Average</li>
<li class="">P95</li>
<li class="">P99</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="">Thread Time</li>
</ul>
<p>By including the professional level tool Tracy Profiler into the Hylozoa source code.
We will then integrate Intel VTune at a later date deeper profiling.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="cpu-miscache">CPU miscache<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#cpu-miscache" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to CPU miscache" title="Direct link to CPU miscache" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>We will first track these sub-metrics:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">L1</li>
<li class="">L2</li>
<li class="">LLC/L3</li>
</ul>
<p>Using <code>perf stat -d hylozoa</code>.
This metric too will be improved by the Intel VTune integration.</p>
<hr>
<h1>🧪 Testing tools</h1>
<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="a-project-of-this-scale-requires-great-testing-the-following-tests-runs-on-our-project">A project of this scale requires great testing, the following tests runs on our project:<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#a-project-of-this-scale-requires-great-testing-the-following-tests-runs-on-our-project" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to A project of this scale requires great testing, the following tests runs on our project:" title="Direct link to A project of this scale requires great testing, the following tests runs on our project:" translate="no">​</a></h4>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="google-tests">Google tests<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#google-tests" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Google tests" title="Direct link to Google tests" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Used for Unit testing.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="google-benchmark">Google benchmark<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#google-benchmark" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Google benchmark" title="Direct link to Google benchmark" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Used for benchmarking certains scenarios.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="gnu-time">GNU Time<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#gnu-time" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to GNU Time" title="Direct link to GNU Time" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Note: we are talking about <code>/usr/bin/time</code> and not the shell built-in <code>time</code>.</p>
<p>A GNU utility tool that display basics stats.</p>
<div class="language-text codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Command being timed: "./hylozoa_engine_main"</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        User time (seconds): 9.47</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        System time (seconds): 1.01</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Percent of CPU this job got: 320%</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Elapsed (wall clock) time (h:mm:ss or m:ss): 0:03.27</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Average shared text size (kbytes): 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Average unshared data size (kbytes): 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Average stack size (kbytes): 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Average total size (kbytes): 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Maximum resident set size (kbytes): 141540</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Average resident set size (kbytes): 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Major (requiring I/O) page faults: 1207</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Minor (reclaiming a frame) page faults: 18592</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Voluntary context switches: 50912</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Involuntary context switches: 66</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Swaps: 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        File system inputs: 212576</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        File system outputs: 96</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Socket messages sent: 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Socket messages received: 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Signals delivered: 0</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Page size (bytes): 4096</span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        Exit status: 0</span><br></div></code></pre></div></div>
<h6 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="an-example-on-the-early-beach-demo-scene">An example on the early beach demo scene<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#an-example-on-the-early-beach-demo-scene" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to An example on the early beach demo scene" title="Direct link to An example on the early beach demo scene" translate="no">​</a></h6>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="tracy-profiler">Tracy Profiler<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#tracy-profiler" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Tracy Profiler" title="Direct link to Tracy Profiler" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>"Tracy is a live profiler for C++ applications that shows frame timings,
thread activity, memory allocations, and CPU hotspots in real time.
It combines manually instrumented zones with statistical sampling to provide both precise timing information and broader performance analysis."</p>
<h6 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="chatgpt-when-asked-to-explain-the-tracy-profilers-github-readme-tagline">ChatGPT when asked to explain the <a href="https://github.com/wolfpld/tracy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">Tracy Profiler's github readme</a> tagline<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#chatgpt-when-asked-to-explain-the-tracy-profilers-github-readme-tagline" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to chatgpt-when-asked-to-explain-the-tracy-profilers-github-readme-tagline" title="Direct link to chatgpt-when-asked-to-explain-the-tracy-profilers-github-readme-tagline" translate="no">​</a></h6>
<p>It offers access to many profiler features by simply including the library and using keywords unto existing code.
These features include:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Thread Visualization</li>
<li class="">GPU Profiling</li>
<li class="">Memory Tracking</li>
<li class="">Frame Analysis</li>
</ul>
<p>It is very effective in CI tests.</p>
<p>It is a high level tools that works best when paired with lower level tools such as:</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="intel-vtune">Intel VTune<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#intel-vtune" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Intel VTune" title="Direct link to Intel VTune" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Intel VTune is a low level CPU &amp; GPU performance analysis tool.
It's main purpose is to investigate and understand performance issues.</p>
<p>It profiles:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Cache misses</li>
<li class="">Branch prediction</li>
<li class="">Pipeline stalls</li>
</ul>
<p>It would not be used directly in CI pipeline.</p>
<hr>
<h1>⚙️ Optimizations</h1>
<h4 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="the-following-optimization-were-done-to-the-project">The following optimization were done to the project:<a href="https://julian52575.github.io/Hylozoa-Engine/blog/performance-optimization#the-following-optimization-were-done-to-the-project" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to The following optimization were done to the project:" title="Direct link to The following optimization were done to the project:" translate="no">​</a></h4>
<p>To be updated alonside completion of the project</p>]]></content:encoded>
